South Africa Not Making ‘Significant Changes’ to Foreign Currency Reserves

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-08-08T09:43:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/south-africa-not-making-significant-changes-to-foreign-currency-reserves.html
South Africa ’s central bank sees “no
reason to make any significant changes” to its foreign currency
reserves holdings after U.S. debt was downgraded by  Standard &
Poor’s  last week, Deputy Governor  Daniel Mminele  said.  The  Reserve Bank  is “monitoring the developments as they
unfold,” Mminele said in an e-mailed response to questions
today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nasreen Seria at 
 nseria@bloomberg.net  